member.name: T:Abodit.StateMachine.StateMachine`3
member.summary:
A state machine allows you to track state and to take actions when states change This state machine provides a fluent interface for defining states and transitions When you inherit from this abstract base class you can add variables to your state machine which makes it an "Extended State Machine"
NB This is a 'curiously self-referencing generic'. This ensures that State objects are not shared across two StateMachines even if they have the same generic arguments. It also makes some syntax nicer and eliminates casting on the consumption side.
NB No state should be stored in the state machine, that is now all stored in the context object.
member.remarks: Also has timed events set to fire at some point in the future but provides no Timer internally because that will be implementation dependent. For example the State may exist in a serialized form in a database with the NextTimedEventAt property exposed for indexing and some external timer fecthing records and calling the Tick() method.
